        <h2>Fashion Souvenirs in Bhutan</h2>
        <p>Most visitors traveling to Bhutan are aware of what to buy or have an idea about the ordinary souvenirs like wood-carved masks, traditional Mandala paintings, prayer flags, or handmade papers. But Bhutan offers more than just the ordinary—especially for those who love fashion and those who like to stand out.</p>
        <p>Bhutan does not fall short of creative and innovative talents who cater to fashionistas always seeking new inspirations to turn streets into runways. Each piece narrates a story—from traditional handlooms to stylish clutches. You won't just be buying a chic purse; you'll be buying stories woven with culture, passion, and heritage.</p>
        <p>From repurposed textiles to cool accessories inspired by ethnicity and tradition, Bhutanese fashion brings together sustainability, storytelling, and style. Below are some top fashion influencers and designers in Bhutan that you should know about while visiting.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Bhutan Street Fashion</h2>
        <p>Bhutan Street Fashion is a photo-based fashion blog that finds inspiration on the streets of Bhutan, portraying an unfiltered sense of modernization. Its creators draw motivation from the everyday lives of Bhutanese people, blending tradition with contemporary expression.</p>
        <p>Through Instagram and Facebook, the blog showcases traditional values and their evolution. It has inspired many Bhutanese youth to fall in love with their heritage costumes and recognize their cultural significance. Launched in 2010, Bhutan Street Fashion continues to grow, connecting Bhutanese fashion to a global audience.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>CDK: Contemporary Bhutanese Clothing Line</h2>
        <p>CDK is a Bhutanese contemporary casual clothing brand based in Thimphu. The name “CDK” is derived from the founder's name, Chandrika. Launched in Fall 2016, the collection incorporates Bhutanese textiles—silk and raw silk—dyed with natural pigments.</p>
        <p>The brand is committed to eco-friendly practices, challenging fashion’s status as one of the world's most polluting industries. CDK offers traditionally inspired daily wear with a modern touch. In addition to clothing, they sell stylish accessories like bags, hand clutches, belts, and stoles—perfect for travelers who want to look classy while supporting local craftsmanship.</p>
        <p>The CDK store is located just above the Craft Bazaar in the capital city, making it easily accessible for visitors.</p>
      </section>
